   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Dataset 2 — UCDP Armed Conflict Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "| | |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Source** | Uppsala Conflict Data Program (UCDP) — one of the world's oldest and most cited conflict databases |\n",
    "| **Coverage** | 2,752 rows × 28 columns, spanning **1946–2024** |\n",
    "| **Format** | Long — one row per **conflict episode** (a distinct active period of a named conflict) |\n",
    "| **What one row means** | A single unbroken active phase of a specific armed conflict in a specific year |\n",
    "\n",
    "A **conflict** in UCDP is defined as a contested incompatibility between a government and at least one other party.\n",
    "\n",
    "The same conflict (e.g. India vs GNLA) can appear as **multiple rows** because conflicts pause and restart — each unbroken active phase is a separate episode with its own start and end date."
   ]
  },
