   "source": [
    "**Key observations:**\n",
    "- Conflicts spiked sharply in **earlier period** compared to the later one.\n",
    "- **Asia (39%) and Africa (33%)** together account for nearly three-quarters of all conflict episodes — concentrated in regions also notable for lower GDP.\n",
    "- **Conflict frequency is cyclical**, with repeated spikes and drops over time.\n",
    "- While **minor conflicts** persist every year, **major conflicts** are relatively rare, indicating that global instability is driven more by frequent low-intensity conflicts than large-scale wars.\n",
    "- **Government of Myanmar (Burma)** was the most involved side in the war \n"
